<item>
            <title>[SHDP-88] HiveScriptRunner swallows exceptions silently</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SHDP-88</link>
                <project id="10801" key="SHDP">Spring for Apache Hadoop</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This block of code in HiveScriptRunner (line 98) swallows exceptions.&lt;br/&gt;
        } catch (Exception ex) {&lt;br/&gt;
            try &lt;/p&gt;
{
                hive.clean();
            }
&lt;p&gt; catch (Exception exc) {            &lt;br/&gt;
            }&lt;br/&gt;
        } finally &lt;/p&gt;
{
            IOUtils.closeStream(reader);
        }
&lt;p&gt;When I have a spring-batch workflow running a Hive job as one of the intermediate steps, I&apos;d like the Hive Tasklet to fail out if something goes wrong, and bubble up an exception so that I can get some meaningful error messages in my logs (and prevent dependent steps from even executing)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
